snippet.textDisplay: I would love a new Kinect. The Kinect had some great tracking software that was very usable in non-gaming environments. When I was doing work as a sub-contractor for a certain, large, corporation, I knew of at least two different groups that went out of their way to buy Kinects in bulk when the announcement for it's discontinuation came out. The Kinect was great for non-touch gesture controls (among other things) when prototyping User Interfaces. There have been some better IR cameras that have come out since it was discontinued, and the PC version of the Xbox One version of the Kinect was prone to stop working when dropped from a height of over 3 meters (it's big and heavy, and prototypes sometimes get built quickly with constant adjustments in mind), but it really is quite handy when paired with Mix-Reality Technologies.
